# Coach-level rules (soft reminders). Two sections:
#   SECTION 1 = PORTABLE CORE — process/diagnostic discipline, NO project facts.
#               Moves to any project unchanged. This is the transferable core.
#   SECTION 2 = PROJECT PRINCIPLES — a general principle + {{facts}} pulled from
#               project.<name>.json. To port: change the facts, not these rules.
# fields: name | when (regex; bilingual matchers — you may prompt in CN or EN) | inject | on?
#
# ===================== SECTION 1: PORTABLE CORE (no facts) =====================
{"name": "debug-method", "when": "为什么|机械音|不对劲?|坏了|没用|还有问题|还不行|debug|诊断|排查|garbage|乱码|杂音", "inject": "[trainlint:don't-guess] This kind of bug is usually SILENT (loss keeps dropping, train/infer are consistently wrong, \"it runs, just bad\"). (1) Default to \"bad output = a silent bug\", not under-training. (2) Pin the symptom to ONE layer (data/encode · decode-render · generation/sampling · training). (3) Reproduce THROUGH the model. (4) Root-cause down to \"a specific line diffed vs the reference\" or \"a probe number\" — ablation is measurement, not a story; don't narrate."}
{"name": "diagnose-rigor", "when": "为什么|为何|找原因|定位|排查|root.?cause|挂了|崩了?|hang|卡死|illegal|OOM|NaN|对比.{0,4}实验|ablation|bisect", "inject": "[trainlint:diagnostic-rigor] (1) Don't guess serially — design >=2 FALSIFIABLE probes and run them in parallel, eliminate by result (serial guessing once took 4h; a bisection took 20min). (2) When a symptom has several variables (storage type / length / dtype / parallelism), change ONE at a time and name the confounds. (3) Don't declare a boundary (\"anything X>Y crashes\") from 2-3 points — build a bisection table."}
{"name": "data-sanity-first", "when": "illegal.?mem|CUDA.?error|backward.*(崩|错|fail)|errno|FileNotFound|读坏|corrupt|NaN|Inf", "inject": "[trainlint:check-data-before-algorithm] When it crashes near IO/NCCL/OOM/NaN, first sample 10 files and load them + check for NaN/magnitude/existence; only AFTER confirming the input is clean, reach for bf16/attention numerical hypotheses. The real cause is often a corrupt read, not sequence length / numerical instability."}
{"name": "repro-at-scale", "when": "修好了|fixed|搞定|解决了|跑通了|应该.{0,3}(好|行|没问题)|work了|没问题了", "inject": "[trainlint:reproduce-at-scale] A 1-step / short-run success != fixed. If the original failure happened at N steps, run >=N steps / at the original scale before declaring victory."}
{"name": "code-not-plan", "when": "架构|怎么实现|工作原理|interleave|讲一下.{0,8}(逻辑|实现|架构|思路)|how.{0,6}(does|work)|design.{0,6}(思路|是)", "inject": "[trainlint:current-code-not-the-plan] Explain an architecture by stating what the code does NOW (file:line + one real trace) BEFORE what's planned; if current and planned differ, flag the gap explicitly."}
{"name": "spot-check-output", "when": "跑完|完成了|finished|生成好了|处理完|job.{0,6}(done|完成)|done\\b", "inject": "[trainlint:spot-check-the-artifact] When a data/processing job finishes, don't trust exit-code + line-count alone. Sample 5-10 output records and check schema/NaN/format/fields before moving to the next stage — bad data silently poisons downstream training."}
#
# ================ SECTION 2: PROJECT PRINCIPLES (general + {{facts}}) ===========
{"name": "train-data", "when": "sbatch|torchrun|run_?train|train\\.(py|sh)|训练|开训|重新?\\s*train|train\\s*吧|去\\s*train|跑.{0,4}(训|模型|实验|run)|launch.{0,10}train", "inject": "[trainlint:verify-target-distribution] Before burning GPU, dump one real sample on CPU and look at the target: (1) no-op/padding is NOT a harmless zero — a frozen tokenizer encodes it to OOD codes that become training targets (check %OOD). (2) Weight the loss for the distribution you WANT at inference; when one class dominates, compute each class's effective gradient share. (3) Confirm the training field is the clean source. This project's traps: {{target_dist_traps}}."}
{"name": "train-infra", "when": "sbatch|torchrun|run_?train|train\\.(py|sh)|训练|开训|重新?\\s*train|train\\s*吧|去\\s*train|跑.{0,4}(训|模型|实验|run)|launch.{0,10}train|多节点|multi.?node|deepspeed|ds_config", "inject": "[trainlint:training-infra] (1) Training reads MUST be on fast, reliable storage ({{good_storage}}); a networked/lazy FS corrupts under concurrent load -> crash; for multi-node, pre-copy to /dev/shm and verify the file count. (2) Config from multiple sources silently overrides — print the EFFECTIVE value ({{config_override_example}}). (3) Hyperparameters don't transfer across regimes ({{regime_example}}). (4) Under ZeRO, a custom sidecar save needs .detach().clone().contiguous() first."}
{"name": "shm-stale-cache", "when": "stage_codes|/dev/shm|--nnodes\\s*=?\\s*[2-9]|ntasks-per-node|多节点.*(暂存|stage)|追加.*(数据|codes)", "inject": "[trainlint:stale-staged-cache] After appending data to a /dev/shm cache that nodes already staged, stale nodes use the old snapshot -> FileNotFoundError -> one rank dies -> multi-GPU NCCL hangs. Staging must COMPARE source vs staged file counts; on mismatch, FORCE_RESTAGE."}
{"name": "fresh-ckpt", "when": "续训|resume|warm.?start|断点续|接着.{0,6}(训|练|ckpt|checkpoint)|从.{0,8}(ckpt|checkpoint).{0,6}(训|练|续|接)|继续训练|continue.{0,6}train", "inject": "[trainlint:don't-continue-a-poisoned-ckpt] A ckpt trained on a wrong target/loss is POISONED ({{poison_example}}). Always retrain fresh from a clean {{reference_impl}} and fix the cause via data/loss/hparams — don't continue-train from a bad ckpt."}
{"name": "demo-discipline", "when": "demo|效果|发我|发你|听.{0,2}听|render|生成.{0,4}音频|\\.wav|感觉.{0,4}(烂|差|怪|好|更)|好像.{0,4}(烂|差|更|不对)|sounds|变差", "inject": "[trainlint:demo/eval-discipline] (1) A demo MUST go end-to-end through the model (generate); never pass off a GT codec round-trip / any proxy as a demo — first point at the line that called model.generate. (2) Label every demo: ckpt-id + which fixes are in it + key preprocessing params ({{demo_param}}). (3) Don't chase a subjective \"sounds worse\" by editing configs — get/produce a concrete sample+ckpt comparison first. (4) Objective metrics only narrow the range; the final call is the ear."}
{"name": "code-align", "when": "\\bloss\\b|权重|weight|speech_mask|\\bmask\\b|ar.?shift|采样|sampler|温度|temperature|kv.?cache|is_causal|duplex/(model|dataset|inference)|modeling_mimo|speech_dataset", "inject": "[trainlint:custom-code-drifts-from-reference] Editing training code = you drifted from a verified reference; assume you broke it: (1) diff line-by-line vs {{reference_impl}}, log a reason for each divergence. (2) AR off-by-one: loss MUST be logits[:,:-1] vs labels[:,1:] — don't echo the input. (3) Every flag that affects the forward pass must match across train/infer and be written into config. This project's traps: {{code_align_example}}."}
{"name": "codec", "when": "encode|编码|mel|tokenizer|codec|codebook|码本|silence|静音|量化|\\bvq\\b|power=|re-?encode|重新.{0,4}编码", "inject": "[trainlint:frozen-component-quirks] A frozen tokenizer/codec is a black box: (1) preprocessing params must match its training config bit-for-bit — don't trust library defaults. (2) no-op regions are OOD — check what they actually encode to. (3) {{codec_quirks}} (4) a weak modality learns a shortcut and ignores the strong condition — quantify with ablation, then add anti-shortcut pressure."}
# --- eval VALIDITY (how to read eval results; general to any model eval) ---
{"name": "eval-metric-by-region", "when": "ablation|accuracy|top-?1|准确率|\\bmetric\\b|指标|评测|\\beval\\b", "inject": "[trainlint:beware-trivial-majority] An aggregate metric can be dominated by a trivially-predictable MAJORITY class (silence/empty/padding). Split it by region: speech vs silence, answer vs pre-answer. We got burned: {{eval_region_example}}."}
{"name": "eval-free-not-tf", "when": "teacher.?forc|tf.?acc|准确率|free.?run|自由生成|teacher 强制|强制解码", "inject": "[trainlint:free-running-is-the-test] Teacher-forced per-cb accuracy OVERSTATES (the past is always GT; continuing the next frame is easy). The real test is free-running autoregressive generation (one sampling error and it collapses). High TF + garbage free-running = the classic shortcut signature."}
{"name": "eval-no-crutch", "when": "onset.?floor|force.?text|forced.?text|blank.*history|crutch|强制.*(起说|文本)|inject.?text|拐杖", "inject": "[trainlint:no-eval-crutch] If a good score depends on help that deployment won't have ({{eval_crutch_example}}), it's not a real score. Eval conditions must EQUAL deployment conditions; label crutched numbers \"holds only under this condition\"."}
{"name": "eval-as-deployment", "when": "offline.*render|streamA_offline|full.?window|streaming|流式|encode_refresh|encode_chunked|离线.*渲染", "inject": "[trainlint:eval-under-deployment-conditions] Offline render / full-window encode measures a DIFFERENT scenario than streaming deployment ({{eval_deploy_example}}). Eval under deployment-equivalent conditions, or run both tracks and label the gap."}
{"name": "concept-gap-quiz", "level": "escalate", "sticky": true, "when": "是啥|什么是|啥意思|什么意思|什么区别|啥区别|有什么.{0,4}(不同|区别)|怎么.{0,4}(理解|区分)|没.{0,4}(解释|讲|说).{0,4}清楚|没.{0,3}(看懂|懂|明白|get)|看不懂|不明白|不太懂|这是.{0,4}干(啥|嘛|什么)|是用来.{0,6}的|what is|what'?s an? |what does .{1,25} mean|what'?s the difference|how do(es)? .{1,30} work|don'?t (get|understand|follow)|confused about|never (heard|seen)", "inject": "[trainlint:concept-gap] A concept just came up that's easy to half-understand — research+engineering is full of them (codec/DAC/s2/RVQ/teacher-forcing…), and a fuzzy one keeps biting silently. Don't just re-explain and move on: (1) QUIZ them FIRST — one sharp question to surface what they actually hold — then (2) define it in PLAIN language (no jargon, why it matters HERE) and correct whatever the answer missed. (3) Record it in research/glossary.<active-project>.jsonl as {term, plain, why} so the gap is tracked, not re-hit."}
